definition.value: Conjugate base of cimicifugic acid K; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of cimicifugic acid D; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of cimicifugic acid J; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of cimicifugic acid E; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A beta-alanine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of beta-alanine with the primary amino group of tryptamine; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A primary ammonium ion obtained by protonation of the primary amino group of  carcinine; major species at pH 7.3.
An organosulfonic acid that is ciprofloxacin  carrying a sulfo group at position 4 of the piperazine ring. It is a metabolite of ciprofloxacin.
Conjugate acid of beta-alanyl-dopamine; major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A low-density lipoprotein that is mildly oxidized and found in the plasma of patients with hypercholesterolemia, diabetes, and acute myocardial infarction. It has been shown to be involved in the pathogenesis of atherosclerosis.

A methyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of varespladib with methanol. It is a potential therapy for the treatment of snakebite envenomings in which toxicity depends on the action of PLA2s.
A methyl glycoside that is alpha-L-fucopyranosyl-(1->3)-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose in which the anomeric hydroxy group is replaced by methoxy.

A branched amino octasaccharide that consists of the linear tetrasaccharide beta-D-Xyl-(1->2)-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the Man residue is substituted at positions 3 and 6 by beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man groups.
An organic radical derived from  octanoic acid.
A  ring assembly that consists of two thiophene rings connected by a single covalent bond.
An octahydronaphthalene that is 1,2,3,4,4a,5,6,7-octahydronaphthalene substituted by isopropyl, methyl, and methylidene groups at positions 1, 4 and 7, respectively (the (1S,4R,4aR)-stereoisomer).
A 1-aci-nitro-omega-(methylsulfanyl)alkane in which the double bond adopts an E-configuration.
A omega-(methylsulfanyl)alkyl desulfoglucosinolate in which the double bond adopts a Z-configuration.
